The EU-Asia Financial Services Roundtable provides a forum for members to: 
1) Exchange information on matters relevant to EU and Asian financial services; 
2) Raise awareness among European and Asian regulators and supervisors on the role of financial services for the respective economies and international trade; 
3) Provide expertise and knowledge to EU and Asian policy-makers, regulators and supervisors on the functioning of financial services; 
4) Advocate, where appropriate, for changes to the regional and international rules to promote trade and the smooth regulatory and supervisory cooperation between the EU and Asian jurisdictions on financial services.
